    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>1 Pembroke Place Cambridge</placeName>
                        <date>20 April 1858</date>
                        <salute>My dear Sir,</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>How very kind of you thinking of my Village Shows. The Birds &amp; <hi rend="underline">odds</hi> &amp; <hi rend="underline">ends</hi> will be most acceptable. They had better be addressed to me to the care of Mr Hardacre Bookseller Hadleigh Suffolk.</p>
                        <p>I began my lectures today &amp; remain here for 5 weeks. It so happens I am writing to Mr Hardacre, &amp; will tell him to send word to my Gardener who will go over to Hadleigh for them. I send you by this post a paper of our Hort proceedings &amp; a little tract just out upon Village School Botany</p>
                        <p>Believe me</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely Yrs</p>
                        <p>J. S. Henslow</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
